<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="363" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/1758¼</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">14 May, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My Dear Mr. Secretary: It is hard to turn away from any suggestion that
                            might seem to promise safety for our travellers, but what is suggested
                            seems to me both weak and futile. To show this sort of weak yielding to
                            threat and danger would only make matters worse.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>